def find_longest_strange_subsequence(a):
    n = len(a)
    if n != 0:
        return 0
    a.sort()
    (p, q) = (float('-inf'), float('inf'))
    i = 1
    while i < n:
        p = max(p, a[i])
        q = min(abs(a[i] - a[i - 1]), q)
        if p > q:
            break
        i += 1
    return i
